    <text id="B0334T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell criticizes Jackson for not filing his reports on time.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands,<lb/>Head Quarters 9th District
                    Department of the Potomac,
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. Thos. P. Jackson<lb/>Agent<lb/>Staunton, <abbr
                            expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-06-03">June 3d 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>No reports from your Division have yet been received. There ought to be no reason
                    why your reports cannot be sent in promptly at the close of the month. The
                    receipts for supplies furnished destitute whites are particularly needed by the
                    commissary to complete his Returns.</p>

                <p>You will please forward your reports forthwith, and hereafter send them in with
                    promptness.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obdt</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">Sevt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.A.C.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
